verbose_text: XREF_BIBR In this previous proof-of-concept study, a TTO signal was flagged if the TTO distribution of a vaccine-event pair differed significantly (at a 0.05 alpha level) from the expected TTO distribution of the [other vaccines]-[event-of-interest] and [vaccine-of-interest]-[other events] pairs within a time window of 30 days after immunisation.
